          "type": "teach",
          "highlight": "Kumusta?",
          "body": "The most common Filipino greeting isn't 'hello.' It's a question."
        },
        {
          "card_id": "ch01_001_s1_c2",
          "type": "teach",
          "highlight": "Kumusta",
          "body": "Kumusta means 'how are you?' You'll hear it everywhere.",
          "example": {
            "tagalog": "Kumusta?",
            "english": "How are you?",
            "note": "Works on its own as a complete greeting."
          },
          "alam_mo_ba_inline": {
            "term": "Kumusta",
            "fact": "Kumusta comes from the Spanish '¿Cómo está?' Over centuries it became its own word.",
            "emoji": "🇪🇸"
          }
        },
        {
          "card_id": "ch01_001_s1_c3",
          "type": "teach",
          "highlight": "Mabuti",
          "body": "Mabuti means 'good' or 'fine.' It's the standard reply to kumusta.",
          "example": {
            "tagalog": "Mabuti.",
            "english": "I'm good.",
            "note": "Simple and natural."
          }
        },
        {
          "card_id": "ch01_001_s1_q1",
          "type": "quiz",
